definitely the COVID crisis that started in March 2020. It impacted our lives with a very important change of the population behavior (more safety habits, less trips outside Spain…). Such an important event will continue generating effects during this 2021, but we at Sisvip believe that, with more responsible and good information sharing, life will slowly become like we used to live it before Covid. That is why we adopt the protection measures that tourism authorities are teaching us, and that we can demonstrate in our Daily Protocol Certified platform.

Let’s take the example of our city, Barcelona. Every day in our city, we can see a great trend of people wanting to live outside of the core city limits and move into locations in the suburban and more natural parts of the city. That is why some of our own employees are also living outside the city center and, even more so, let me tell you that some of us live in small towns close to Barcelona territory. We wanted to know why this became such a trend that has dominated the past time Lisbon community. Isn’t life easier living closer to work? Do you think this will have a long-term impact on the behavior of any Lisbon community? Prepared for answers?
